H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>, There is sufficient evidence to say that) the data has not been drawn from the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">N</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>88</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>75</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math> distribution.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <strong><em>R0A1</em></strong>.</p>\n<p>The conclusion to part (e)(ii) <strong>MUST</strong> follow through from their hypotheses seen in part (d); if hypotheses are incorrect/reversed etc., the answer to part (e)(ii) must reflect this in order for the <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>to be credited.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13512746","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ1.3eii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, perform the test to a 5 % significance level, clearly stating the conclusion in context.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.9—Normal distribution and calculations","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}